<span id="freeTextContainer12337329144849305679">I had mixed feelings about this book; in part b/c it was billed as a good summer read / feel good romance, which it really wasn&apos;t at all. The history part regarding WWII in Italy was very interesting, and the food bits were fabulous. The romance was good, but there were a few trite, worn-out misunderstandings that I could have done without. <br/><br/>It did have, as so many other books and movies, a good &quot;<a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/130916.The_Saving_Graces_A_Novel' title='The Saving Graces A Novel by Patricia Gaffney' rel='nofollow noopener'>saving grace</a>&quot; ending which almost made it rank a bit higher, but not enough for me. <br/><br/>Perhaps if I had </span>
  <span id="freeText12337329144849305679" style="display:none">I had mixed feelings about this book; in part b/c it was billed as a good summer read / feel good romance, which it really wasn't at all. The history part regarding WWII in Italy was very interesting, and the food bits were fabulous. The romance was good, but there were a few trite, worn-out misunderstandings that I could have done without. <br /><br />It did have, as so many other books and movies, a good "<a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/130916.The_Saving_Graces_A_Novel" title="The Saving Graces A Novel by Patricia Gaffney" rel="nofollow noopener">saving grace</a>" ending which almost made it rank a bit higher, but not enough for me. <br /><br />Perhaps if I had expected more of the war information: the heartbreak, the sacrifice, the evils of society, I might have enjoyed it more.</span>
