<span id="freeTextContainer3644110429111734285">I loved this book too! What a delight. The story of a love affair between a British officer and his tempestuous Italian cook in the final years of the Second World War, it would make a wonderful movie. I&apos;d pay to see it, for sure. I&apos;ve read two earlier books by Anthony Capella, The Food of Love and The Empress of Icecream, and like them, this book is full of fabulous descriptions of food. I cooked my family an Italian feast once I&apos;d finished this book, though I had to look up some of the recipes</span>
  <span id="freeText3644110429111734285" style="display:none">I loved this book too! What a delight. The story of a love affair between a British officer and his tempestuous Italian cook in the final years of the Second World War, it would make a wonderful movie. I'd pay to see it, for sure. I've read two earlier books by Anthony Capella, The Food of Love and The Empress of Icecream, and like them, this book is full of fabulous descriptions of food. I cooked my family an Italian feast once I'd finished this book, though I had to look up some of the recipes on the internet. I can't believe this book is not better known – it should be. One of the best books so far this year. </span>
